    <h1>Code Leap Privacy Policy</h1>
    <div>Effective date: <strong> 28/10/2025 </strong>
    </div>


    <div>   
    <p>This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>Code Leap</strong> ("we", "us", "our") collects, uses, and protects personal data when you use our website and services. We are committed to protecting your privacy and complying with the UK General Data Protection Regulation (UK GDPR).</p>


    <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
    <p><strong>Data Controller:</strong> Code Leap Ltd<br>
    <strong>Registered address:</strong> [Insert Company Address, UK]<br>
    <strong>Contact email:</strong> <a href="mailto:[email@example.com]">[email@example.com]</a></p>


    <h2>2. Information we collect</h2>
    <ul>
    <li><strong>Account & profile:</strong> name, email, phone, CV, education, employment history, skills, portfolio links.</li>
    <li><strong>Applications:</strong> cover letters, jobs applied for, messages exchanged with employers/recruiters.</li>
    <li><strong>Technical & usage:</strong> IP address, device/browser information, pages visited, cookies.</li>
    <li><strong>Optional:</strong> sensitive data you choose to provide (e.g. equal-opportunity data).</li>
    </ul>


    <h2>3. How we collect data</h2>
    <ul>
    <li>Directly from you when you register, apply, or contact us.</li>
    <li>Automatically when you use the platform (cookies and analytics).</li>
    <li>From third parties if you sign in with social accounts or if employers provide data.</li>
    </ul>


    <h2>4. How we use your data</h2>
    <p>We process personal data to:</p>
    <ul>
    <li>Create and manage accounts, and provide our services.</li>
    <li>Match candidates with job opportunities and share applicant information with employers when you apply.</li>
    <li>Send transactional messages (e.g., application updates) and - with consent - marketing communications.</li>
    <li>Improve and secure the platform (analytics, fraud prevention).</li>
    </ul>


    <h2>5. Legal bases for processing</h2>
    <p>We rely on the following legal bases under UK GDPR:</p>
    <ul>
    <li><strong>Contract:</strong> to provide the services you requested.</li>
    <li><strong>Legitimate interests:</strong> platform improvements, security, and personalised job suggestions (balanced against your rights).</li>
    <li><strong>Consent:</strong> for marketing communications and optional special categories of data.</li>
    <li><strong>Legal obligation:</strong> where required by law.</li>
    </ul>


    <h2>6. Sharing your information</h2>
    <p>We may share personal data with:</p>
    <ul>
    <li>Employers and recruiters when you apply for a job.</li>
    <li>Service providers (hosting, analytics, email, payment processors).</li>
    <li>Regulatory, legal or government authorities when required.</li>
    <li>Third parties in the event of a merger or sale (with safeguards).</li>
    </ul>


    <h2>7. International transfers</h2>
    <p>Some providers may process data outside the UK. We use appropriate safeguards such as Standard Contractual Clauses or rely on adequacy decisions to ensure your data remains protected.</p>


    <h2>8. Data retention</h2>
    <p>We retain personal data for as long as necessary to provide services and meet legal obligations. By default:</p>
    <ul>
    <li>Active accounts: retained while the account is active.</li>
    <li>Deleted accounts: retained up to 12 months after deletion for legal or fraud prevention reasons (unless a different retention is required).</li>
    <li>Anonymous/aggregated data: may be kept indefinitely for analytics.</li>
    </ul>


    <h2>9. Your rights</h2>
    <p>You have rights under UK GDPR, including: access, correction, deletion, restriction, objection, portability, and withdraw consent. To exercise these rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:[email@example.com]">[email@example.com]</a>. <br>
    We may need to verify your identity before responding.</p>


    <h2>10. Cookies & tracking</h2>
    <p>We use cookies to make the site work and to give you a better experience. You can manage cookie settings in your browser. For more detail, see our <strong>Cookie Policy</strong> (link).</p>


    <h2>11. Security</h2>
    <p>We implement technical and organisational measures to protect personal data. No system is completely secure, but we continually review and improve our security.</p>


    <h2>12. Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this policy from time to time. We will notify users of material changes by email or via a notice on the platform.</p>


